{{Infobox College Mascot | name = Citronaut | image = | image_size = 175px | caption = {{small|Original Mascot of the [[University of Central Florida]]}}<ref group="note">Then-Florida Technological University.</ref> | university = University of Central Florida | conference = American Athletic Conference | conference_short = The American | description = Anthropomorphic [[Orange (fruit)|orange]] | name_origin = | first_seen = Fall {{start date and age|1968}} | related_mascots = [[Knightro]], Glycerin {{small|(retired)}}<ref name="knightro">[http://ucfathletics.cstv.com/trads/ucf-trads-knightro.html Knightro is born. UCF Athletic Association.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071027171048/http://ucfathletics.cstv.com/trads/ucf-trads-knightro.html |date=2007-10-27 }}</ref> | official_website = | hall_of_fame = }}
The '''Citronaut''' was the first mascot of Florida Technical University, which later became The [[University of Central Florida]]. The mascot appeared on the first student handbook in 1968–1969.<ref>[http://www.ucfknights.com/news/2007/4/19/UCF_Receives_Knighthood.aspx UCF Receives Knighthood. UCF Athletic Association.]</ref><ref>[http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/one-small-step-man-one-giant-leap-ucf/ One Small Step for Man, One Giant Leap for UCF. [[Pegasus (University of Central Florida magazine)|Pegasus]]]</ref> After one year, students petitioned the [[Student Government]] to establish a new mascot for the university. In 1970, students approved "Knights of the Pegasus" as the second official university mascot, which remains to this day.<ref name="knightro"/>
==History== The Citronaut was designed by Norman Van Meter, the brother-in-law of FTU's then-president [[Charles N. Millican]] in an attempt to combine the two major themes of Central Florida at the time: the [[NASA|space program]] and the [[Citrus production|citrus industry]]. UCF was founded in 1963 to provide personnel to support [[NASA]] at the [[Kennedy Space Center]] and [[Cape Canaveral Air Force Station]]. As the academic scope of the university broadened, it was renamed to The University of Central Florida in 1978.<ref name="2000_facts">{{cite web|url=http://www.iroffice.ucf.edu/character/char0001.html|title=Facts About UCF - 2000–2001|accessdate=July 14, 2009|publisher=University of Central Florida|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100531013846/http://www.iroffice.ucf.edu/character/char0001.html|archivedate=May 31, 2010|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://uaps.ucf.edu/enrollment/current_projections_enrollment.html |title=UCF Enrollment Projections 2012-17 |accessdate=August 19, 2013 |publisher=University of Central Florida |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051212054318/http://uaps.ucf.edu/enrollment/current_projections_enrollment.html |archivedate=December 12, 2005 |df= }}</ref> Additionally, Florida produces approximately 100 million boxes of citrus annually.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Perez|first1=Marvin|title=Orange Juice Enters Bull Market With Biggest Rally Since ’98|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-03-24/orange-juice-enters-bull-market-with-biggest-rally-since-1998|accessdate=25 March 2015|work=[[Bloomberg News]]|date=24 March 2015}}</ref>
==Modern Appearances== Since 2014, the Citronaut has experienced a renaissance in university publications, athletics programing, and merchandise.<ref>[http://today.ucf.edu/knights-baseball-team-welcomes-back-citronaut/ Knights Baseball Team Welcomes Back the Citronaut. University of Central Florida.]</ref><ref>[http://www.ucfknights.com/news/2015/9/19/Citronauts_on_Top.aspx Citronauts on Top. UCF Athletic Association.]</ref><ref>[http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/knights-in-space/ Knights in Space. University of Central Florida.]</ref>
May 10th, 2014 - UCF Baseball proclaimed Citronaut Day<ref>http://today.ucf.edu/knights-baseball-team-welcomes-back-citronaut/</ref>
September 19th, 2015 - UCF Men's Soccer played in fauxback Citronaut uniforms <ref>http://www.ucfknights.com/news/2015/9/19/Citronauts_on_Top.aspx</ref>
Spring 2016 - Knights in Space <ref>http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/knights-in-space/</ref>
November 2018 - Space Game - Citronaut appears on uniforms of the UCF football team against Temple. <ref>https://ucfknights.exposure.co/a-familiar-flight</ref> {{Gallery |width=175 | height=200 |align=center |File:CjdvOZQXEAAkjC2.jpg |Modern Citronaut costume. }}
