'''Uzbekistan''' was one of the [[Turkvision Song Contest 2013#Participating countries and regions|twenty-four participating countries and regions]] competing in the first Turkvision scheduled to take place between the 17 and 21 December 2013.

==History==
Uzbekistan made their debut in the Turkvision Song Contests at the {{Tscyr|2013}} festival, in [[Eskişehir]], [[Turkey]].<ref name="Participation">{{cite web|last=Granger|first=Anthony|title=Participating Countries Revealed|url=http://eurovoix.com/2013/10/19/turkvizyon-2013-participating-countries-revealed/|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=25 October 2013|date=19 October 2013}}</ref> The contest was not broadcast on television in Uzbekistan. [[Nilufar Usmonova]] was selected internally to represent Uzbekistan in Turkey,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Uzbekistan: Nilufar Usmonova Off To Turkvizyon|url=http://eurovoix.com/2013/12/07/uzbekistan-nilufar-usmonova-off-to-turkvizyon/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> it had previously been announced that [[Shahzoda]] would represent Uzbekistan with the song "Medlenno" (Медленно).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Uzbekistan: Shahzoda Will Represent Uzbekistan|url=http://eurovoix.com/2013/11/12/uzbekistan-shahzoda-will-represent-uzbekistan/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>

On 22 July 2015 Uzbekistan confirmed participation in the contest, [[Tarona Records]] were announced as being in charge of Uzbek participation.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Anthony|first1=Granger|title=Uzbekistan: Turkvizyon 2014 Participation Confirmed|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/07/22/uzbekistan-turkvizyon-2014-participation-confirmed/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> Aziza Nizamova was announced on 3 November 2014,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Uzbekistan: Aziza To Kazan|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/11/03/uzbekistan-aziza-to-kazan/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> she sang "Dunyo bo'lsin omon" (Дунё бўлсин омон).<ref>{{cite web|title="TURKVIZYON-2014," the premier international competitions spectator TARONA|url=http://popcorn.uz/index.php?newsid=1172|website=Popcorn.uz|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>

